{"uuid":"7d218eb8-a79d-46d4-85ef-efdb1a528aba","parentUuid":"60eb66b2-6fa6-4d25-a9c5-fb3d740d2eb1","sessionId":"302b4314-6f2d-4150-b37b-ea90f04a041a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T02:07:33.026Z","type":"assistant","cwd":"C:\\Users\\linhl","version":"0.14.0","model":"coder-model","message":{"role":"model","parts":[{"text":"The user wants to know how to create skills, so I should explain the concept, directory structure, and required files for creating a custom skill.","thought":true},{"text":"To create a custom skill in Qwen Code, follow these steps:\n\n## Creating a Custom Skill\n\n1. **Create a skill directory** in your project:\n   ```\n   .qwen/skills/<your-skill-name>/\n   ```\n\n2. **Add a `SKILL.md` file** as the main definition:\n   ```markdown\n   ---\n   name: my-skill\n   description: A brief description of what this skill does\n   ---\n   \n   # My Skill\n   \n   Instructions for the AI on how to use this skill.\n   ```\n\n3. **Add supporting files** (optional):\n   - `scripts/` - Shell/Python scripts to execute\n   - `references/` - Reference documentation\n   - `templates/` - Code templates\n   - Any other resources the skill needs\n\n4. **Reference the skill** in your `.qwen/settings.json` (if needed for auto-loading)\n\n## Example Structure\n```\n.qwen/skills/\n└── my-custom-skill/\n    ├── SKILL.md          # Required: skill definition\n    ├── scripts/\n    │   └── helper.sh\n    └── references/\n        └── docs.md\n```\n\n## SKILL.md Format\n```markdown\n---\nname: skill-name\ndescription: Short description (shown when user asks for this skill)\n---\n\n# Skill Name\n\nDetailed instructions, examples, and context for the AI to follow.\n```\n\nWould you like me to help you create a specific skill?"}]},"usageMetadata":{"promptTokenCount":14239,"candidatesTokenCount":360,"thoughtsTokenCount":29,"totalTokenCount":14599,"cachedContentTokenCount":13767},"contextWindowSize":1000000}
